        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 5:17PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 517 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Knoxville, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Knoxville, Maryville, Alcoa, Louisville, Rockford, Eagleton Village,
Karns, Lake Forest, Bearden, and Powell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
